HEADWORD: Seminymph
<hw>Sem"i*nymph`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>The pupa of insects which undergo only a slight change in passing
to the imago state.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

